\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Colossus. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Colossus' attack is a horizontal line that naturally matches the formation of enemy units, which automatically line up next to each other when attacking. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This attack design was originally introduced with the argument that it should reward micro-management and proper positioning. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Unfortunately, positioning is usually automatically correct, and maps as well as classic unit compositions severely limit the room for creative positioning. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a result, it almost never happens that Colossi approach from a different direction than the main army. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Since Colossi cannot defend themselves against air units, yet can be attacked by pure anti-air units, they are far too vulnerable to move around on their own. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In practice, the idea of flexible positioning does not fit the reality of gameplay. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
It feels more like a punishment when a Colossus is not standing directly inside the main army to deal optimal damage, for example, when a newly built Colossus reinforces from a different angle. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Even their cliff-walking ability is hardly usable, because, again, they are too vulnerable when alone, especially against air units, and there are too few units like Stalkers that can follow them over cliffs by using Blink. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
I don't know for sure, but I could imagine that Blizzard's original idea was that the Colossus should function on many maps like a combination of Shuttle and Reaver from StarCraft: Brood War, except that the Colossus cannot move over water and thus has more limitations, giving players a reason to sometimes still use a Warp Prism for transportation. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To return to its weapon, Dustin Browder said in 2009 that: "The original attack is not coming back. The old beam was just 'more damage.' Simple, but not fun. The current Colossus weapon encourages micro since it really matters who you shoot and the angle you shoot them from. Fortunately since the Colossus can step up and down cliffs and over friendly units he can move to the optimal position if you are fast enough." <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
For me, this falls into a similiar category as: "Do you guys not have phones?" <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Do you often see players having fun with Colossus positioning? <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Do you see many interesting positional plays against deathballs that show a clear difference between beginners and professional players? <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
I simply don't. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Maybe most players just aren't fast enough. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
That is why the Colossus weapon is now again a continuous single-target attack, similar to a Sentry beam, but with automatic target locking and area-of-effect damage that also works against air units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The target lock ensures that the weapon has extended range as long as the Colossus continues attacking the same enemy unit. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
If the target or Colossus moves outside that extended range, the continuous beam breaks. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This makes the Colossus flexible enough to operate alone on the map and hold its own against any unit type, although there are still dedicated counters that can take it down efficiently. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Additionally, the new weapon deals damage while moving, which is useful both when chasing and when retreating, and it makes micro with the Colossus genuinely enjoyable. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
You try to activate the attack, but immediately keep moving so the Colossus stays out of range of enemy units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The new danger posed by the Colossus also makes it an interesting harassment unit. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Opponents need to hunt it down and can counter the attack effectively if they maintain proper spacing between units to avoid the splash damage. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Overall, this creates more interesting micro on both sides and allows for more diverse unit compositions.}
