\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In this video, I'll explain why the Mothership has been removed from the game and why it has been replaced by the Arbiter. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Mothership is a unit that you can only build once, which automatically means it has to be stronger than other units, since its power cannot come from mass production like it does for all other units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Unfortunately, this also leads to tactical and strategic limitations, because you can't use its abilities in multiple locations or multiple times across different army groups. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Due to its strength, the Mothership usually becomes a priority target, as it always represents the highest threat on the battlefield. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Unfortunately, this causes the entire game to revolve around this single unit, which actually reduces overall diversity. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Additionally, I simply prefer the Arbiter model over the Mothership model, which is a very subjective reason, but not the only one. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Arbiter's smaller model improves visibility on the battlefield. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
For these reasons, and because it wouldn't feel appropriate to have multiple Motherships, and because its large model obscures too many units and reduces visual clarity, it has been replaced by the Arbiter. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Arbiter can be built multiple times, deals bonus damage to armored units and structures, and its abilities cost energy instead of having cooldowns. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This makes the Arbiter useful in more situations and gives it more counters. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Now let's take a look at its abilities. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Instead of having a passive cloaking effect, the Arbiter, just like the Mothership, has Cloaking Field, which makes the Arbiter and all nearby friendly units invisible for a limited duration. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The fact that the Arbiter itself also becomes invisible makes it harder to counter, but it also enables ambushes that wouldn't be possible with a visible Arbiter. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a result, detection and good scouting become increasingly important. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Draining the Arbiter's energy early and using area-of-effect damage that works on cloaked units become important tools against it. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The next ability is Time Warp, which now increases the movement and attack speed of all units inside the field instead of slowing them. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This change was made because Protoss already have plenty of abilities that restrict enemy movement, such as the Obelisk slow, Force Field, and Stasis Ward. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This version of Time Warp is also more counterable, because there are more ways to push units out of it than there are ways to force units into it. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a result, players are incentivized to push enemy units out and move their own units in to benefit. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This increases player interaction, can lead to more varied outcomes in matches, and scales well with player skill when contesting specific areas. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The final ability is Transference, which replaces Mass Recall. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Transference teleports all nearby friendly units into a Psionic Matrix. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This allows units to not only escape dangerous situations, but also, with the help of a Warp Prism, to be teleported behind enemy lines. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Additionally, units can be teleported not just to a Nexus, but anywhere a Psionic Matrix exists. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This makes the ability significantly more flexible and opens up more tactical and strategic possibilities. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Overall, the Arbiter is a support unit that improves mobility and enhances friendly units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\f6\dbch\af10\loch
These new options enable fresh tactical responses and strategic depth.}
